Two of the four accused in the Amy-Leigh de Jager kidnapping case have informed the court they intend pleading guilty. eNCA's Aviwe Mtila is at the high court sitting in Palm Ridge for us. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Two of the four people accused in the Amy-Leigh de Jager kidnapping are going to plead guilty. Tharina Human and Laetitia Nel have been charged with abducting the child, at Laerskool Kollegepark in Vanderbijlpark a year ago. The accused pair have informed the High Court sitting in Palm Ridge that they intend to plead. READ: Apprehended alleged kidnapper reveals syndicate Six-year-old Amy-Leigh was found wandering the streets some 19-hours later. The case resumes on Thursday.